uk.ac.liv.jmzqml.xml.io

Class MzQuantMLMarshaller

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.liv.jmzqml.xml.io.MzQuantMLMarshaller

  • public class MzQuantMLMarshaller
extends Object
    Class for marshalling an mzQuantML file.

    An mzQuantML file can be marshalled in two different ways. One way is to marsharl the whole mzQuantML object into a file; the other way is to use helper methods to stitch together large XML elements.

      • marshall

        public void marshall(MzQuantML mzQuantML)
        Marshalling of a whole MzQuantML object.

        This method marshals an whole mzQuantML object to the file whose name is used to create the MzQuantMLMarshaller.

        Parameters:
        mzQuantML - the MzQuantML object to be marshalled.

      • createBibliographicReferenceTag

        public String createBibliographicReferenceTag(String id,
                                     String name,
                                     String authors,
                                     String publication,
                                     String publisher,
                                     String editor,
                                     Integer year,
                                     String volume,
                                     String issue,
                                     String pages,
                                     String title,
                                     String doi)
        The helper method creates a tag of BibliographicReference with all the attributes. The id attribute of BibliographicReference is mandatorily required. The other attributes are optional.
        Parameters:
        id - (required) An identifier is an unambiguous string that is unique within the scope (i.e. a document, a set of related documents, or a repository) of its use.
        name - (optional) The potentially ambiguous common identifier, such as a human-readable name for the instance.
        authors - (optional) The names of the authors of the reference.
        publication - (optional) The name of the journal, book etc.
        publisher - (optional) The publisher of the publication.
        editor - (optional) The editor(s) of the reference.
        year - (optional) The year of publication.
        volume - (optional) The volume name or number.
        issue - (optional) The issue name or number.
        pages - (optional) The page numbers.
        title - (optional) The title of the BibliographicReference.
        doi - (optional) The DOI of the referenced publication.
        Returns:
        a BibliographicReference string tag, representing bibliographic references.

      • createCv

        public Cv createCv(String id,
          String fullName,
          String uri,
          String version)
        The helper method creates a Cv object with all the attributes. The id, fullName and URI attributes of Cv are mandatorily required. The version attributes is optional.
        Parameters:
        id - (required) The unique identifier of this cv within the document to be referenced by cvParam elements.
        fullName - (required) The full name of the CV.
        uri - (required) The URI of the source CV.
        version - (optional) The version of the CV.
        Returns:
        the Cv object, a source controlled vocabulary from which cvParams will be obtained.

      • createCvParam

        public CvParam createCvParam(String name,
                    String cvRef,
                    String accession,
                    String value,
                    String unitAccession,
                    String unitName,
                    String unitCvRef)
        The helper method creates a CvParam object with all the attributes. The name, cvRef (String type) and accession attributes of CvParam are mandatorily required. The other attributes are optional.
        Parameters:
        name - (required) The name of the parameter.
        cvRef - (required) A string reference to the CV element from which this term originates.
        accession - (required) The accession or ID number of this CV term in the source CV.
        value - (optional) The user-entered value of the parameter.
        unitAccession - (optional) An accession number identifying the unit within the OBO foundry Unit CV.
        unitName - (optional) The name of the unit.
        unitCvRef - (optional) If a unit term is referenced, this attribute MUST refer to the CV 'id' attribute defined in the cvList in this file.
        Returns:
        the CvParam object, a single entry from an ontology or a controlled vocabulary.
